            "data_validation_policy_details_4" => "We will retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.",
            "email" => [
                "policy_details" => "As soon as you register with SJ Panel, you authorize us to send you the account activation link and once you activate your account by clicking on the link sent in the account activation e-mail, you authorize us to send survey invitations, newsletters, reward information, notifications and company updates to the e-mail address you provided to the company at the time of registration.",
                "policy_heading" => "E-mail Opt-In Policy"
            ],
            "link" => [
                "details" => "Our Site includes links to other Web sites whose privacy practices may differ from those of SJ Panel. If you submit personally identifiable information to any of those sites, your information is governed by their privacy policies. We encourage you to carefully read the privacy policy of any Web site you visit.",
                "heading" => "Links to 3rd Party Sites"
            ],
            "modification" => [
                "policy_details" => "SJ Panel reserves the right to change its privacy policy at anytime. As soon as the privacy policy is changed or modified, it will be updated on the website under privacy policy section. If SJ Panel makes any material changes in the privacy policy, you will be notified via email and prior to the changes becoming effective. Privacy policy update notification will also be published on our website. You are advised to review all changes to any policy. This does not affect your statutory rights.",
                "policy_heading" => "Change or Modification of Privacy Policy"
            ],
            "personal_identity_details_1" => "The personal identifiable information collected by SJ Panel is only used for market research studies and for no other purposes. SJ Panel does not sell or share personally identifiable information of its panel members or of individuals who are not registered with us to any third party without your prior consent. If personally indefinable information is required in any research surveys, there will be a DND Agreement (Do Not Disclose Agreement) signed between SJ Panel and the client to avoid the further usage and dissemination of the data. Also, SJ Panel asks you for your consent to participate in such surveys before sending you to the end-client. Participating in such surveys is completely at your discretion.",
            "personal_identity_details_2" => "We will share your personal information with third parties only in the ways that are described in this privacy policy. We do not sell your personally identifiable information to third parties.",
            "personal_identity_details_3" => "We may provide your personally identifiable information to companies that provide services to help us with our business activities such as reward management, customer support (helpdesk), email delivery or shipping your order. These companies are authorized to use your personally identifiable information only as necessary to provide these services to us, and to fulfil our obligations to you.",
            "personal_identity_details_4" => "In certain situations, SJ Panel may be required to disclose personal data in response to lawful requests by public authorities. We may also disclose your personally identifiable information as required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process and when we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.",
            "personal_identity_details_5" => "If SJ Panel is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of its assets, you will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our Web site of any change in ownership or usage of your personally identifiable information, as well as any choices you may have regarding your personally identifiable information, including the right to be forgotten.",
            "personal_identity_heading" => "Use of Personally Identifiable Information",
            "security" => [
                "details" => "SJ Panel ensures that all the collected information from its members and users are secured on the server with best available technology. Personally identifiable information of the members and users is restricted and accessible to appropriate and designated members of SJ Panel. We maintain optimum level of security of personally identifiable information submitted to us, both during transmission and once received. We keep personally identifiable information encrypted in our database and use SSL encrypted methods for data transmission. No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, however. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.",
                "heading" => "Security Policy"
            ],
            "sign" => [
                "details" => "You can log in to our site using sign-in services such as Facebook Connect or an Open ID provider. These services will authenticate your identity and provide you the option to share certain personally identifiable information with us, such as your name and email address, to pre-populate our sign-up form. Services like Facebook Connect give you the option to post information about your activities on this Web site to your profile page to share with others within your network.",
                "heading" => "Single Sign-On"
            ],
            "tracking_technologies_details_1" => "We and our market research partners, affiliates, analytics service providers or tracking technology partners use technologies such as :cookies, beacons, tags and scripts. These technologies are used in analyzing trends, administering the site, tracking users’ movements around the site and to gather demographic information about our user base as a whole. We may receive reports based on the use of these technologies by these companies on an individual as well as aggregated basis.",
            "tracking_technologies_details_2" => "We use cookies to remember users’ settings (e.g. language preference), for authentication. Users can control the use of cookies at the individual browser level. If you reject cookies, you may still use our site, but your ability to use some features or areas of our site may be limited.",
            "tracking_technologies_details_3" => "IP addresses are tied to personally identifiable information to identify your geo location in order to provide suitable survey for you and prohibit respondents from non-qualifying region/area/countries/places.",
            "tracking_technologies_details_4" => "We partner with a third party to either display advertising on our website or to manage our advertising on other sites. Our third-party partner may use cookies or similar technologies in order to provide you advertising based upon your browsing activities and interests. If you wish to opt out of interest-based advertising, click here.",
            "tracking_technologies_heading" => "Tracking Technologies",
            "unsubscribe" => [
                "policy_details" => "If you choose to de-activate your membership with “SJ Panel” or to require us to cease processing your personal data, you may automatically discontinue your membership by clicking on Unsubscribe after logging-in to “SJ Panel”. By following the appropriate directions, your record will be marked as “do not contact”, and you will no longer receive communications from “SJ Panel”. In addition, we will forfeit any incentive balance that has not been requested as the time you opt out. Please allow two to three business days for processing of this change. In the meantime, you may receive Emails from us and we apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. As an alternative, you may send an Email directly to privacy@sjpanel.com requesting to be removed. We will retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.",
                "policy_heading" => "Opt-Out or Unsubscribe Policy"
            ],
            "widget_heading" => "Widgets",
            "widgets_details" => "Our Web site includes Social Media Features, such as the Facebook Like button [and Widgets, such as the Share this button or interactive mini-programs that run on our site]. These Features may collect your IP address, which page you are visiting on our site, and may set a cookie to enable the Feature to function properly. Social Media Features and Widgets are either hosted by a third party or hosted directly on our Site. Your interactions with these Features are governed by the privacy policy of the company providing these features."
        ],
        "sjpanel_ask_details_1" => "E-Mail: SJ Panel requires your email address to contact you for the surveys, reward information, newsletters, company updates and notifications.Date of Birth: We request you to provide this so that we can update your age automatically and invite you to participate in a suitable survey.Social Profile URL (LinkedIn/Facebook/Twitter/Google), Company name, ID proof, Profile picture (Optional): It will help SJ Panel to authenticate your identity and avoid duplicate registration.",
        "sjpanel_ask_details_2" => "Gender, Education Level, Household Income, Employment Status, Ethnic Background, Race, Religion, Zip Code/Postcode/Pin Code::SJ Panel collects this information from you so that we can invite you to participate in a suitable and relevant survey.",
        "sjpanel_ask_details_3" => "Physical Address: It is collected so that SJ Panel can contact you to participate in a product testing survey. Product testing survey is a type of survey where we can send the product to your physical address to use the product and share your feedback. The product will be sent to you only if you agree to participate in such surveys.",
        "sjpanel_ask_details_4" => "Other Personal and Consumer Information: It is collected so that SJ Panel can invite you to participate in a research survey with the qualifying criteria that best matches to your profile information.",
        "sjpanel_ask_details_5" => "If you are not a member of SJ Panel and SJ Panel collects the personal identification information upon your consent (like e-mail ID, Date of Birth, Gender, Household Income, Education Level, Employment status, State/Province Zip Code/Postcode/Pin Code and IP Address), the only reason is to route you to the right surveys matching the information. SJ Panel asks for your email ID so that we can inform you when you qualify for a survey and/or win the sweepstakes. If you have opted for follow-up surveys, we may contact you in cases where we need additional feedback for a particular survey that you had qualified earlier. Apart from this there is no other reason to collect your personally identifiable information. Also, your personally identifiable information will ONLY be held for as long as necessary to complete the purpose for which it was collected. Your information will be deleted once the purpose of information collected is met.",
        "sjpanel_ask_heading" => "SJ Panel asks following information:",
        "sjpanel_commitment_details" => "SJ Panel is an online market research survey data collection website dedicated to provide high quality data to market research firms and other data collection companies. Protection of your privacy and confidentiality is SJ Panel's top priority. The data that SJ Panel collects is used only for market research purpose and SJ Panel always reviews or publishes it in a Pseudonymized or Anonymized format or as aggregate information (about a group/groups). Individual information is never disclosed without your prior consent as it is irrelevant to the research conducted by SJ Panel or SJ Panel's clients. Registering as a member of SJ Panel does not constitute consent. Also, your information is not disclosed to any other individual, or third party, directly from SJ Panel.",
        "sjpanel_commitment_heading" => "Our Commitment",
        "sjpanel_owner_details" => "(\"SJ Panel\") is owned and operated by RS Sample Junction LLP (\"DBA Sample Junction\"). Sample Junction is a partnership firm based in Delhi registered with The Ministry of Corporate Affairs, India, and adheres to the rules and regulations of the Limited Liability Partnership Act 2008. Sample Junction owns and operates the website www.sjpanel.com and its sub-domains.",
        "sjpanel_owner_details_1" => "SJ Panel is firmly committed to protect your privacy and avoid the dissemination of your personally identifiable information, in accordance with international regulations including, but not limited to The EU-U.S. and Swiss-U.S. Privacy Shield Frameworks, GDPR and ISO. You can directly contact us via e-mail in case of any concerns related to our privacy practices at privacy@sjpanel.com.",
        "sjpanel_personal_info_details" => "At the time of registration SJ Panel asks you to provide your basic personally identifiable information. Once you are registered, SJ Panel further asks you to update more personal and profiling information which helps us to find suitable surveys for you.",
        "sjpanel_personal_info_heading" => "Personal Identifiable Information"
    ],
    "privacy_policy_2" => [
        "details_1" => "(\"SJPanel\")is owned and operated by RS Sample Junction LLP (\"DBA Sample Junction\"). Sample Junction is a partnership firm based in Delhi registered with The Ministry of Corporate Affairs, India, and adheres to the rules and regulations of the Limited Liability Partnership Act 2008.",
        "details_2" => "Sample Junction owns and operates the website www.sjpanel.com and its sub-domains.",
        "details_3" => "SJPanel is firmly committed to protect your privacy and avoid the dissemination of your personally identifiable information, in accordance with international regulations including, but not limited to the EU-U.S. and Swiss-U.S. Privacy Shield Frameworks, GDPR and ISO.",
        "details_4" => "RS Sample Junction LLP respects and understands the importance of your privacy – and are therefore committed to provide complete protection to the personal information of our panelists who use our services or visitors of our website, and of the candidates whose information we may have access to and when you apply on our website for an open position. It is in recognition of this need for security, our commitment to EU GDPR and Secured management of any information received /collected by us that RS Sample Junction LLP has established this Privacy Policy.",
        "details_5_1" => "For residents of the State of California, please click",
        "details_5_2" => "here",
        "details_5_3" => "to find out more about your rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 (“CCPA”) and our compliance.",
        "question_1" => [
            "heading" => "WHAT INFORMATION IS COLLECTED AND WHY?",
            "point_1" => "Personal Information Collected on Our Website",
            "point_1_details" => "As a general practice, no personal Information is collected about a visitor to the website, apart from the personal information submitted by the visitor himself/herself in a ‘contact us’ form or. We shall use such Personal Information for the purpose you share it with us. However, at times, certain information may be collected from you when you visit the website. Such information is aggregated to measure the number of visits, average time spent on the website, pages viewed etc. This gives us an idea of which parts of our website users are visiting, in order that we may improve the content to offer you better services. We do not link IP addresses to anything personally identifiable. This means that a user’s session will be tracked, but the user will be anonymous.",
            "point_2" => "Information collected at the time of Panelist registration",
            "point_2_details" => "Protection of your privacy and confidentiality is SJPanel's top priority. The data that SJPanel collects is used only for market research purpose and SJPanel always reviews or publishes it in a Pseudonymized or Anonymized format or as aggregate information (about a group/groups). Individual information is never disclosed without your prior consent as it is irrelevant to the research conducted by SJPanel or SJPanel's clients. When you register with us as a panelist, SJPanel asks you to provide your basic personally identifiable information. Once you are registered, SJPanel further asks you to update additional personal and profiling information which helps us to find suitable surveys for you.",
            "point_2_details_1" => "SJPanel asks following information during registration:",
            "point_2_details_1_age" => "Age:",
            "point_2_details_1_age_details" => "To contact you for the surveys, reward information, newsletters, company updates and notifications.",
            "point_2_details_1_email" => "E-Mail:",
            "point_2_details_1_email_details" => "To contact you for the surveys, reward information, newsletters, company updates and notifications.",
            "point_2_details_1_physical" => "Physical Address:",
            "point_2_details_1_physical_details" => "It is collected so that SJPanel can contact you to participate in a product testing survey. Product testing survey is a type of survey where we can send the product to your physical address to use the product and share your feedback. The product will be sent to you only if you agree to participate in such surveys.",
            "point_2_details_1_social" => "Social Profile URL (LinkedIn/Facebook/Twitter/Google), Company name, Profile picture and ID Proof (Optional):",
            "point_2_details_1_social_details" => "to verify authenticate your identity and avoid duplicate registration and avoid identity theft.",
            "point_2_details_1_special" => "Special categories of Personal information:",
            "point_2_details_1_special_details" => "When you register with us we ask you to update your profile with some optional information that may be classified as special or sensitive personal information example- Ethnic Background, Race, Religion, sexual orientation etc. SJPanel collects this information from you so that we can invite you to participate in a suitable and relevant survey. We only process this information upon your consent.",
            "point_3" => "Tracking Technologies-",
            "point_3_details" => "We and our market research partners, affiliates, analytics service providers or tracking technology partners use technologies such as: cookies, beacons, tags and scripts. These technologies are used in analysing trends, administering the site, tracking users’ movements around the site and to gather demographic information about our user base. We may receive reports based on the use of these technologies by these companies on an individual as well as aggregated basis.",
            "point_3_details_1" => "We use cookies to remember users’ settings (e.g. language preference), for authentication. Users can control the use of cookies at the individual browser level. If you reject cookies, you may still use our site, but your ability to use some features or areas of our site may be limited.",
            "point_3_details_2" => "IP addresses are tied to personally identifiable information to identify your geo location in order to provide suitable survey for you and prohibit respondents from non-qualifying region/area/countries/places.",
            "point_4" => "Sample Junction Emails- Panelist",
            "point_4_details" => "We do contact our registered panelists as a part of our campaigns and periodically for sending transactional information about your account with us and on upcoming surveys and rewards. We do not do any mass mailing and carefully reach out to selected professional with a personalized approach., you can opt out of receiving such emails by clicking on the unsubscribe button.",
            "point_5" => "Buttons or Tools on Our Websites Related to Other Companies and Social Media Pages",
            "point_5_details" => "Our websites may include buttons or tools that link to other companies’ services (for example, a Facebook or Google button). We may collect information about your use of these features. In addition, when you see or interact with these buttons, tools, or content, or view a SJPanel web page containing them, some information from your browser may automatically be sent to the other company. Please read that company’s privacy policy for more information, as these sites may have their own privacy statements in place, which we recommend you review if you visit any linked Web sites. We are not responsible for the content of linked sites or any use of the sites or for the privacy practices of those other Web sites.\n We may collect information when you interact with our social networking pages or use the sign-on features.",
            "point_6" => "Data Validation Policy",
            "point_6_details" => "Frequently or from time to time SJPanel conducts the data validation of its panel members, to ensure the quality of survey data, honesty and integrity of responses and uniqueness of members. SJPanel reserves the rights to terminate the membership of any panelist(s) and restrict the user(s) to participate in future surveys from SJPanel, if any discrepancy is found in the process of data validation.",
            "point_6_details_1" => "As soon as you update you profile, you will be invited to the research surveys that match your newly updated information.",
            "point_6_details_2" => "We will retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements."
        ],
        "question_2" => [
            "details" => "Information and data files are stored on our servers and the servers of companies we hire to provide services to us. We do not share, sell or lease any kind of information collected to any third parties for their marketing uses.",
            "heading" => "WHERE DO WE STORE THIS DATA?"
        ],
        "question_3" => [
            "details" => "We use this information to:",
            "details_1" => "In all cases this information is not shared with any third party. It is used by SJPanel as above or to prevent/respond to protection of our websites or applications. In some cases, like with hosted services, we may share information with those that provide us with technology services (e.g. web hosting and analytics services), but strictly for the purpose of carrying out our work. All such vendors used by us are EU GDPR compliant and have signed a Data protection agreement with SJPanel to secure your data. We may be required to share information with law enforcement or other third parties when compelled to do so by court order or other legal process, to comply with statutes or regulations.",
            "details_2" => "If we merge with or are acquired by another company, and if all of our assets are acquired by another company, this information will most likely be one of the assets to be transferred. However, we will not transfer any personal information of our customers until absolutely necessary to provide you with a continuity of service and only when the new owner maintains and provides the same level of data privacy standards as we do. In such cases, we will provide you with notice and an opportunity to opt-out of the transfer of identifiable data.",
            "heading" => "HOW DO WE USE THE INFORMATION COLLECTED?",
            "list_1" => "To send you custom tailored surveys as per your demography and interests allowing you to earn and redeem rewards.",
            "list_2" => "To fulfil our contractual commitment and to enhance the performance of our contract with you.",
            "list_3" => "Provide you with the services, support or information requested and monitor effectiveness of our online survey program.",
            "list_4" => "Improve our website’s user experience and communicate better to engage users",
            "list_5" => "To process your job application for an open position.",
            "list_6" => "Analyze, diagnose and fix issues in our service offerings"
        ],
        "question_4" => [
            "details_1" => "We understand that the security of your information is vital and have in place strong administrative, technical, and physical security controls and measures to keep data safe and secure. Our privacy practices are designed to provide protection for your personal information, all over the world.",
            "details_2" => "To protect information stored in our servers, through secured server infrastructure at various locations like the US, Australia and India, access is limited (through user/password credentials and two factor authentication) to those employees who require it to perform their job functions. We use industry-standard Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption technology to safeguard the account registration process and sign-up information. Other security safeguards include but are not limited to multifactor authentication, data encryption, firewalls, and physical access controls to building and files.",
            "details_3" => "We would like to caution our visitors about phishing attacks, wherein unscrupulous third parties seek to extract sensitive and confidential information from you by posing as a genuine website or by sending an email misrepresenting it to be from a genuine source. Please be aware that we never seek sensitive or confidential information such as regarding your financial or health record through emails or through our websites. If you receive such a message claiming to be from SJPanel, then please do not reply to it and immediately bring it to our attention by contacting the DPO <a href='mailto:privacy@sjpanel.com'>(privacy@sjpanel.com)</a>.",
            "details_4" => "SJPanel also recognizes the receipt, transmission or distribution of spam emails (unsolicited bulk emails) as a major concern and has taken reasonable measures, to minimize the transmission and effect of spam emails in its computing environment.",
            "heading" => "HOW DO WE SECURE INFORMATION COLLECTED?"
        ],
        "question_5" => [
            "details_1" => "In some cases, and at our discretion this information may be accessed by respective organizations to correct any mistake in that information, and to delete any information we no longer have business reasons for retaining. You can do this by sending us an email. SJPanel strives to comply with all applicable laws around the globe that are designed to protect your privacy and information, no matter where that information is collected, transferred, or retained. Although legal requirements may vary from country to country, we intend to adhere to the principles set forth in this Privacy Policy even if information is transferred from your country to other countries that may not require an adequate level of protection for your information.",
            "heading" => "CAN THIS INFORMATION BE REVIEWED?",
            "point_1" => "RIGHTS OVER YOUR PERSONAL DATA",
            "point_1_details" => "Under certain circumstances, by law you have the right to:",
            "point_1_details_1" => "If you would like to contact us in relation to any of the rights set out above please contact us by email <a href='mailtio:privacy@sjpanel.com'>privacy@sjpanel.com</a>.To protect your privacy and security, we may take reasonable steps to verify your identity before providing you with the details.",
            "point_1_list_1" => "Be informed about the processing of your personal data (i.e. for what purposes, what types, to what recipients it is disclosed, storage periods, any third party sources from which it was obtained, confirmation of whether we undertake automated decision-making, including profiling, and the logic, significance and envisaged consequences).",
            "point_1_list_10" => "Any request for access to or a copy of your personal data must be in writing and we will endeavor to respond within a reasonable period and in any event within one month in compliance with Data Protection Legislation. We will provide this information free of charge unless the request is manifestly unfounded or excessive. We will comply with our legal obligations as regards any individual’s rights as a data subject.",
            "point_1_list_2" => "Object to your personal data being processed for a particular purpose or to request that we stop using your information.",
            "point_1_list_3" => "Request not to be subject to a decision based on automated processing and to have safeguards put in place if you are being profiled based on your personal data.",
            "point_1_list_4" => "Ask us to transfer a copy of your personal data to you or to another service provider or third party where technically feasible and otherwise required by applicable regulations.",
            "point_1_list_5" => "Withdraw, at any time, any consent that you have previously given to us for our use of your personal data.",
            "point_1_list_6" => "Ask us to stop or start sending you marketing messages at any time.",
            "point_1_list_7" => "Request access to your personal data (commonly known as a \"data subject access request\"). This enables you to receive a copy of the personal data we hold about you and to check that we are lawfully processing it.",
            "point_1_list_8" => "Request correction of the personal data that we hold about you. This enables you to have any incomplete or inaccurate information we hold about you corrected. It is important that the personal data we hold about you is accurate and current. Please keep us informed if your personal data changes during your working relationship with us.",
            "point_1_list_9" => "Request the erasure of your personal data. This enables you to ask us to delete or remove personal data where you think that we do not have the right to process it.",
            "point_2" => "RIGHT TO COMPLAIN TO THE ICO",
            "point_2_details_1" => "You can contact the ICO if you have any concerns about how SJPanel has handled your personal data and you also have the right to make a complaint at any time to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), the UK supervisory authority for data protection issues. You can contact the ICO via their helpline on 0303 123 1113. You can find out more information about your rights as a data subjects, their regulatory powers and actions they can take on their website",
            "point_3" => "NOTIFICATION OF CHANGES",
            "point_3_details_1" => "If we decide to change our privacy policy, we will post those changes on this page, so our users are always aware of the information we collect and how we use it. If at any point we decide to use personally identifiable information in a manner different from that stated at the time it was collected, we will notify users by way of an email. Users will have a choice as to whether or not we use their information in this different manner. We will use information in accordance with the privacy policy under which the information was collected.",
            "point_3_details_2" => "Where links are provided to other websites it should be noted that they are not and cannot be governed by our Privacy Statement. We cannot guarantee your privacy when you access other websites through any link provided on this website."
        ]
    ],
    "rewards" => [
        "details_merchants" => "The merchants represented are not sponsors of the rewards or otherwise affiliated with SJ Panel. The logos and identifying marks of these trademarks are owned by each represented brand and/or its affiliates.",
        "heading_1" => "SJ Panel Rewards Redemption Methods",
        "heading_2" => "SJ Rewards",
        "heading_3" => '<p style="font-size:16px;">Explore the enticing world of survey rewards with SJ Panel, a rewarding panel that offers a plethora of opportunities for participants to earn quick rewards. Dive into the realm of SJ Rewards, where your opinions are valued and rewarded generously. SJ Panel opens the doors to a wide array of redemption options, ensuring that your valuable insights are duly recognized and compensated.<br><br>With SJ Panel’s Online Survey Rewards Program, participants can embark on a journey of earning rewards simply by sharing their opinions on various topics. Discover the best survey rewards available in the market and unlock exciting incentives with each survey completed.<br><br> Upon completing surveys and accumulating rewards, participants receive redemption coupons via their registered email. These coupons, provided by<a href="https://www.bhnrewards.com/rewards-gifts/" target="_blanks" style="text-decoration:none" > Rybbon</a>, offer flexibility in choosing how to redeem your hard-earned incentives. Start earning rewards for your opinions today and indulge in the satisfaction of claiming your well-deserved rewards. </p>'
    ],
    //reward policy added by munesh on 19 april 2023 for all languages *******************************start here *************************
    "reward_policy" => [
        "details_reward_policy_title"=>"SJ Panel | Reward Policy | SJ Rewards",
        "details_referral_policy_title"=>"SJ Panel | Referral Policy",
        "details_terms_condition_title"=>"Terms and Conditions",
         "details_terms_condition_title_update"=>"updated on : ",
          "details_referral_policy_title_various"=>"Various stages of our referral program: ",
         
        
        "details_reward_policy" => "SJ Panel is owned and maintained by RS Sample Junction LLP (or 'Sample Junction') and provides online panel services through the website #SJPANELURL. This website #STREPLACE1 is owned and maintained by RS Sample Junction LLP. All individuals associated with the SJ panel are subject to the following policy and are requested to please read the below Reward Policy carefully and start using the website only if you understand and agree with everything stated below.",
        "details_reward_policy_1" => "Only members who are registered and have approved accounts with the SJ Panel are eligible to use and earn rewards from the site. Any participation without having an approved account won’t earn you any rewards from our site.",
        "details_reward_policy_2" => "Reward points will be credited to your SJ Panel account only if you qualify and complete a survey. Your points will be credited to your account as soon as the client approves your survey completion and data. This may take a few days or a few weeks.",
        "details_reward_policy_3" => "You must contact our helpdesk team if you don’t see the reward in your account after getting the message that 'Your responses on survey #xxxxxxx have been successfully approved by our client and your points have been credited to your SJ Panel account.'",
        "details_reward_policy_4" => "Your responses to the survey will be checked upon its closure, and if we find any junk or fake responses, any fraud tricks used while taking the survey, or if you have provided answers in a straight line without properly reading the questions, or if your answers don’t make any sense logically or practically, your survey rewards will be removed, and it may lead to your disqualification from the panel.",
        "details_reward_policy_5" => "If we find your survey responses rejected three (3) or more times, it may lead to the permanent rejection of your account, and you will be blacklisted from our panel. After your account being marked as 'backlisted':",
        "details_reward_policy_6" => "All your unclaimed rewards will be forfeited immediately.",
        "details_reward_policy_7" => "You will be restricted from participating in any future survey thereafter with the SJ Panel.",
        "details_reward_policy_8" => "'The claim redemption request' which is in process, will still be executed and you will get reward coupon in your email as per the normal procedure.",
        "details_reward_policy_9" => "You can redeem your earned points once your points are approved. It may take 15–30 days to process your redemption request. You will be notified once your redemption request is approved.",
        "details_reward_policy_10" => "To redeem your earned points, you need to reach the minimum threshold for redemption, which is 5000 points.",
        "details_reward_policy_11" => "The reward amount earned from referrals becomes redeemable when the person referred by you is approved for survey participation and if he or she qualifies in his or her first survey.",
        "details_reward_policy_12" => "To redeem your points, please visit the Points Redemption ⇒ Redeem Points section in your account and choose any of the available reward options at the time of making a redemption request. Please know that for reward distribution, SJ Panel uses a third-party company called 'Rybbon'.",
