    "safeguard" => [
        "address" => "CANADA Office # 117, 9131 Keele St ,Concord, ON L4K 0G7",
        "heading1" => "Safeguards",
        "heading_3" => "Working together to keep your data secure",
        "heading_4" => "SJ Panel’s responsibilities",
        "heading_5" => "Shared responsibility",
        "heading_4_1" => "Build security into our architecture",
        "heading_5_1" => "Cloud Architecture",
        "heading_5_2" => "Secure networks",
        "heading_5_3" => "Safe Access",
        "heading_5_4" => "Maintain employee security and privacy awareness",
        "heading_5_5" => "Breach notification",
        "heading_5_6" => "Anonymous Access",
        "heading_5_7" => "Password Storage",
        "heading_5_8" => "Sharing Passwords",
        "heading_5_9" => "Physical Security to Control Information Access",
        "heading_5_10" => "Backup and Disaster Recovery",
        "heading_5_11" => "Right To Search And Monitor",
        "heading_5_12" => "Personal Use",
        "heading_5_13" => "Violations",
        "para_1" => "#SJPANELURL('SJ Panel') is owned and operated by RS Sample Junction LLP (doing business as “Sample Junction”) We work with our panelists to keep their data secure. We take comprehensive measures to protect our infrastructure, network, and applications; train employees in security and privacy practices; build a culture where being worthy of trust is the highest priority; and put our systems and practices through rigorous third-party testing and auditing.<br>
                        While “SJ Panel” is responsible for securing each aspect of the service that’s under our control, panelists play a key role in ensuring their data are protected and secure.<br>
                        We’ve put together this guide to help you understand what “SJ Panel” does to keep your account safe, and what you can do to maintain visibility and control over your data",
        "para_2" => "Thousands of panelists around the world trust us. To earn that trust, we work hard to build secure standards you can rely on. Here are some of the ways that we secure our architecture and networks.",
        "para_3" => "'SJ Panel' uses cloud network architecture to ensure safeguard of your data",
        "para_4" => "Strict limitation is maintained between the internal 'SJ Panel' network and the public Internet through a cloud firewall. Access to the production environment is restricted to only authorized workers and requires authentication on all endpoints",
        "para_5" => "All employees at 'SJ Panel' are assigned unique ids, user level and must have 10 characters strong password to access our tools.<br>
                        Limit employee access to backend systems.<br>
                        Our tools are crafted in accordance with user level, so only an authorized person has access to services they can access/perform. We make sure that 'SJ Panel' employee access to our internal systems is strictly controlled. Access between our corporate and production networks is strictly limited.",
        "para_6" => "Part of keeping our service secure is making sure that people who work at 'SJ Panel' understand how to be security conscious and recognize suspicious activity. To that end, 'SJ Panel' employees are required to acknowledge security policies prior to being granted systems access. Employees also take part in mandatory security and privacy training for new hires and annual follow-up training, and receive regular security awareness training via informational emails, talks, presentations, and resources available on our end.",
        "para_7" => "'SJ Panel'  will notify you in the event of a data breach, as required by applicable law. We maintain incident response policies and procedures, including a breach notification process, which enables us to notify affected customers as needed.",
        "para_8" => "'SJ Panel' doesn’t allow any anonymous access to its tools which means for each and every person, there is a common gateway to get access to the tools and applications.",
        "para_9" => "'SJ Panel' disallows any kind of readable storage of passwords, passwords must be changed in an interval of 90 days and are stored as 256 bit AES encryption.",
        "para_10" => "Sharing of passwords is not allowed. If an admin need access to certain employee account, he must have a written request from department head, worker is then assigned a temporary password, which is later changed.",
        "para_11" => "Every sensitive machine at workplace is kept out of reach to prevent unauthorized access.",
        "para_12" => "'SJ Panel' uses cloud-based backup technique and backups are transferred in a secure socket layer protocol and are end to end encrypted.",
        "para_13" => "'SJ Panel' has rights to search and monitor any employee machine.",
        "para_14" => "Personal use of business machines is disallowed at 'SJ Panel'.",
        "para_15" => "'SJ Panel' employees who willingly and deliberately violate this policy will be subject to disciplinary action up to and including termination."


    ],
